revision.text:
{{italic title}} '''''Conspectus of the ornithological fauna of the USSR''''' ({{ISBN|5-02-005300-7}}) is a 1991 [[Russian language]] publication by [[ornithologist]] [[L. S. Stepanyan]].
It contains a list of bird species recorded from the former [[Soviet Union]], together with details of their [[range (biology)|distribution]], [[Taxonomy (biology)|taxonomic relationships]] and [[subspecies]].
==Taxonomic changes==
The following is a list of the species [[splits & lumps]] proposed by Stepanyan:<ref>Voous (1977) is used for this comparison</ref>
* [[Siberian herring gull]] (''Larus heuglini''), together with the race ''vegae'' to be regarded as a separate species from [[European herring gull|herring]] and [[lesser black-backed gull]]s. * [[Asian short-toed lark|Asian]] and [[lesser short-toed lark]]s to be regarded as separate species * [[Yellow-headed wagtail|Yellow-headed]] (''Motacilla lutea''), [[Green-headed wagtail|green-headed]] (''M. taivana'') and [[Western yellow wagtail|black-headed]] (''M. feldegg'') wagtails split from [[Western yellow wagtail|yellow wagtail]] (''M. flava'') * [[Masked wagtail|Masked]] (''Motacilla personata'') and [[Black-backed wagtail|black-backed]] (''M. lugens'') wagtails split from [[white wagtail]] (''M. alba'') * [[Eastern great tit|Eastern great]] (''Parus minor''), [[Turkestan tit|Turkestan]] (''P. bokharensis''), and [[Grey tit|Grey]] (''P. cinereus'') tits split from [[great tit]] (''P. major'') * [[Grey-bellied bullfinch|Ussuri (oriental, grey-bellied)]] (''Pyrrhula griseiventris'') and [[Grey bullfinch|grey]] (''P. cineracea'') bullfinches split from [[common bullfinch]] (''P. pyrrhula'')
