[[File:FN2A3007.jpg|thumb|300px|The calving end of a [[glacier]] at a fjord in [[Novaya Zemlya]].]] [[File:Akhmatowa-Fjord 1 2014-08-30.jpg|thumb|300px|View of [[Akhmatov Fjord]], [[Bolshevik Island]], Severnaya Zemlya.]] [[File:Мистерия Авачинской Бухты.JPG|thumb|300px|View of a fjord in southeastern [[Kamchatka]].]] This is a list of the most important [[fjord]]s of the [[Russian Federation]]. ==Fjords== In spite of the vastness of the Arctic coastlines of the federation there are relatively few fjords in Russia. Fjords are circumscribed to certain areas only; over thirty are in [[Novaya Zemlya]] —including lakes which are structurally fjords, with a few others in the [[Barents Sea]] coast of the [[Kola Peninsula]], the [[Severnaya Zemlya]] archipelago, the [[Bering Sea]] coast of the [[Chukchi Peninsula]]<ref>P. Brovko et al. in ''The Diversity of Russian Estuaries and Lagoons Exposed to Human Influence'' edited by Ruben Kosyan, p. 64</ref> and the southeastern shores of [[Kamchatka]].<ref>Kaplin, P.A., ''Fjord coasts of the Soviet Union.'' Publishing House of the [[USSR Academy of Sciences]], Moscow 1962</ref> {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Akhmatov Fjord]], Bolshevik Island, Severnaya Zemlya * [[Ara Bay]], Kola Peninsula * [[Arkhangelskaya Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Guba Arkhangel’skaya">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13507768|title=Guba Arkhangel’skaya|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Bezymyannaya Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Bezymyannaya">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13498606|title=Guba Bezymyannaya|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Blafyel Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Bukhta Blaf’yel’">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13498044|title=Bukhta Blaf’yel’|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Bolshaya Karmakulskaya]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Guba Bol’shaya Karmakul’skaya">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13495764|title=Guba Bol’shaya Karmakul’skaya|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Bolshaya Volokovaya]], [[Kola Peninsula]] * [[Borzov Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Borzova">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/15363394|title=Zaliv Borzova|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Brandt Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar77">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 77</ref> * [[Chekin Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar78">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 78</ref> * [[Dolgaya Shchel]], Kola Peninsula * [[Goltsovoye Lake]], Novaya Zemlya (a lake with a fjord structure)<ref name="mapcarta-Ozero Gol’tsovoye">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/14072578|title=Ozero Gol’tsovoye|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Gribovaya Bay]] (Gribovii Fjord), Novaya Zemlya * [[Inostrantsev Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref>JaapJan Zeeberg, ''Into the Ice Sea: Barents' Wintering on Novaya Zemlya'', Purdue University Press 2005, p. 207</ref> * [[Khutuda Fjord]], [[Taymyr Peninsula]]<ref name="mapcarta-F’ord Khutuda">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/15434174|title=F’ord Khutuda|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=23 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Kislaya Guba]], Kola Peninsula * [[Kola Bay]] (Murmansk Fjord), Kola Peninsula * [[Klokov Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Klokova">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13440538|title=Zaliv Klokova|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Krestovaya Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref>Mark Nuttall, ''Encyclopedia of the Arctic'', p. 1872</ref> * [[Krivoshein Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Krivosheina">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13427502|title=Zaliv Krivosheina|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Lednikovoye Lake]], Novaya Zemlya (a lake with a fjord structure)<ref>[http://blogs.agu.org/fromaglaciersperspective/2016/08/29/lednikovoye-glaciers-novaya-zemlya-1999-2016-retreat/ AGU - Lednikovoye Glaciers, Novaya Zemlya 1999–2016 retreat]</ref> * [[Litke Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Litke">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13415222|title=Zaliv Litke|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Maka Bay]], Novaya Zemlya * [[Malaya Volokovaya]], Kola Peninsula * [[Marat Fjord]], [[October Revolution Island]], Severnaya Zemlya * [[Mashigin Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Guba Mashigina">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13403294|title=Guba Mashigina|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Matochkin Shar]], Novaya Zemlya (a strait with a fjord structure)<ref>Alexander P. Lisitzin, ''Sea-Ice and Iceberg Sedimentation in the Ocean: Recent and Past'', p. 449</ref> **[[Meta Bay]], a northern branch of Matochkin Shar * [[Matusevich Fjord]], [[October Revolution Island]], Severnaya Zemlya * [[Medvezhy Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar78">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 78</ref> * [[Mityushikha Bay]] (Mytyushev Bay), Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Губа Митюшиха">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13397728|title=Guba Mityushikha|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Neznayemy Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar78">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 78</ref> * [[Nordenskiöld Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Nordenshel’da">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13385684|title=Zaliv Nordenshel’da|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Northern Sulmenev Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Guba Severnaya Sul’meneva">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13338472|title=Guba Severnaya Sul’meneva|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Oga Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Oga">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13378032|title=Zaliv Oga|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Partizan Fjord]], Bolshevik Island, Severnaya Zemlya * [[Pechenga Bay]], Kola Peninsula * [[Penkigney Bay]], Chukchi Peninsula * [[Polisadov Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Bukhta Polisadova">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/15433820|title=Bukhta Polisadova|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=17 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Providence Bay]], Chukchi Peninsula * [[Pukhov Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Pukhovyy">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13354094|title=Zaliv Pukhovyy|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Russkaya Bay]], Kamchatka<ref name="mapcarta-Bukhta Russkaya">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/16600308|title=Bukhta Russkaya|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Russkaya Gavan' Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref>[https://www.researchgate.net/publication/227809199_Glacier_extent_in_a_Novaya_Zemlya_fjord_during_the_Little_Ice_Age_inferred_from_glaciomarine_sediment_records Glacier extent in a Novaya Zemlya fjord during the “Little Ice Age” inferred from glaciomarine sediment records]</ref> * [[Serebryanka fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref>[https://www.google.co.th/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&rlz=1C1NHXL_thTH686TH686&ion=1&espv=2&ie=UTF-8#q=Gribovii+Fjord Ice-free conditions in Novaya Zemlya 35 000–30 000 cal years BP]</ref> * [[Sedov Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar79">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 79</ref> * [[Shubert Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Залив Шуберта">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13332968|title=Zaliv Shuberta|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Southern Sulmenev Bay]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Guba Yuzhnaya Sul’meneva">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13277810|title=Guba Yuzhnaya Sul’meneva|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Spartak Fjord]], Bolshevik Island, Severnaya Zemlya * [[Stepovoy Fjord]], Novaya Zemlya<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Stepovogo">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/13320712|title=Zaliv Stepovogo|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=18 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Tarya Bay]], Kamchatka<ref name="mapcarta-Bukhta Tar’ya">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/16587130|title=Bukhta Tar’ya|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=19 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Tereza Klavenes Fjord]], [[Taymyr Peninsula]]<ref name="mapcarta-Zaliv Terezy Klavenes">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/16376390|title=Zaliv Terezy Klavenes|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=23 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Thaelmann Fjord]], Bolshevik Island, Severnaya Zemlya * [[Tsivolko Bay]] (Ziwolka Fjord), Novaya Zemlya<ref name="prostar79">''Prostar Sailing Directions 2005 North Coast of Russia Enroute'', p. 79</ref> * [[Tumannaya Bay]], Bolshevik Island, Severnaya Zemlya * [[Ura Bay]], Kola Peninsula * [[Vera Bay]], Novaya Zemlya * [[Vilkitsky Bay]], Novaya Zemlya * [[Vilyuchin Bay]], Kamchatka<ref name="mapcarta-Vilyuchinskaya Bukhta">{{cite web|url=http://mapcarta.com/16585244|title=Vilyuchinskaya Bukhta|work=Mapcarta|accessdate=19 December 2016}}</ref> * [[Voryema Bay]], Kola Peninsula * [[Zapadnaya Litsa River|Zapadnaya Litsa]], Kola Peninsula {{div col end}}
