==Most prominent summits==
{{GeoGroup|section=Most prominent summits}}
{{see also|List of the ultra-prominent summits of Alaska}}
Of the 100 most prominent summits of Alaska, only Denali exceeds {{convert|4000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence, six peaks exceed {{convert|3000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}, 26 peaks exceed {{convert|2000|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}, [[List of the ultra-prominent summits of Alaska|65 peaks are ultra-prominent summits with at least {{convert|1500|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}}]], and all 100 peaks exceed {{convert|1066|m|0|abbr=off|comma=5|sp=us}} of topographic prominence.  Four of these peaks lie on the international border with [[British Columbia]] and four lie on the international border with [[Yukon]].
{{clear}}
